snippet.textDisplay:
A huge, hugely underrated point about these new artists, ESPECIALLY those like Uzi, is that the live experience greatly, if not disproportionately, influences the perception of the music.

Having seen Uzi live, I find myself banging to the songs harder than those that haven't, in an inherent acknowledgement that they were made to cater to the sound and energy of the live experience that is bound to come.
